The paper deals with image filtering and machine learning, specifically in the context of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to optimize the filters, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of crowdsourcing and inter-dataset generalization, which could potentially place it in the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
